      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Presenting an investment-grade FD3S Mazda RX-7, featuring the legendary 13B-REW rotary engine in its most refined state. This specimen maintains its original sequential twin-turbocharger setup, exhibiting zero shaft play and delivering a seamless transition between the primary and secondary boost phases. The complex vacuum control system has been meticulously overhauled with high-temp silicone lines to ensure rock-solid idle stability and precise boost control. Compression numbers are optimal across all rotor faces, verified by a recent thermal-compensated test. The chassis remains structurally perfect, retaining its factory 50/50 weight distribution, supported by original double-wishbone suspension with refreshed bushings. The drivetrain is rounded out by a tactile five-speed short-throw gearbox and a Torsen limited-slip differential, both showing no signs of synchro wear or gear whine. This is a rare, unmolested example of 90s JDM engineering excellence.",
